<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 2:15PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Walker and
northeastern Chattooga Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 215 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Lafayette, moving
southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Trion, Naomi, Center Post, Subligna, Suttles Mill and
Villanow.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
